messages.text: So, have you guys picked a date yet?
I know. Did I send you a pic of the ring?
Thanks. I know, I love it!
Does this mean you guys are going to move in soon?
The neighborhood’s really getting iffy so the sooner the better.
Oh, nothing. Just lately a lot of people have been bothering me.
There’s this old woman I keep seeing.
She kept asking me where I got it.
Maybe she wants to get one like it.
Anyway, I have a meeting. Talk soon.
That old woman was here again.
The one from your old neighborhood?
Do you think she’s following me???
I left Daniel’s townhouse and headed to work.
I’m halfway down the block when I see her.
And she knew my name this time!!!
She’s like, Becca, so good to see you.
I’d like to see that ring again!
I told her my ring was none of her business and she says
I kept walking and when I turned to look back.
Maybe you should call the police.
And say what? There’s an old lady following me???
I got home from work and she was HERE!!!
I don’t know!! The alarm system was set!!!
She said she knows it’s hers and she wants it back.
And then she said I had to get away from him.
That he was going to hurt me.
Yes. Except she called him Dr. Hartley.
I told her it was my ring and she had to leave.
Then she went into our bedroom and pulled this box out of the closet.
How did she know it was there?
I have no idea. Where did all that jewelry came from?!?!
I told Daniel and he said he would come straight home.
Do you need me to come over?
It’s ok. I think that’s him now.
He’s throwing the jewelry in a bag and he says we have to leave.
Go somewhere safe. I’m calling the cops.
Did you do what I said?
I locked myself in the bathroom.
I can hear him talking to someone.
Idk. He keeps saying you’re dead. Leave us alone.
He’s pleading with me to open it.
He says he needs the ring or they’ll catch him!!!
He’s trying to break the door down!!!
I hear them. They’re arresting him.
They tied most of the jewelry to his patients.
Some of them died of natural causes.
it makes me sick thinking about it.
What did you do with the ring?
I kept looking for the old lady.
Finally, one day I found her on the steps.
I asked her if she wanted it back.
She smiled and said I could keep it.
I took the ring and tossed it in the river.
I hope I never see it or her again.
